        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:42PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 242 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Smiths Crossroad, or
near Lagrange, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mountville, Lagrange, Big Springs, Louise, Baughs Crossroads,
Odessadale, and Smiths Crossroad.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
